[h1]Marry a Local Noble - Continued[/h1]

Adds the option to marry your dynasty's characters to a randomly generated local noble for a flat cost of [b]25 ducats[/b]. Useful when there are no suitable suitors available and you refuse to despoil your bloodline with lowborn rabble.

This is an updated and fixed version of [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3600093580]Kaiser's original mod[/url], rewritten from scratch for compatibility with [b]version 1.1.x[/b].

[h2]Features[/h2]
[list]
[*]Works for both [b]male and female[/b] recipients
[*]Created noble shares the recipient's [b]culture and religion[/b], so they are truly local
[*]Flat cost of [b]25 ducats[/b]
[*]AI will use this interaction to keep old rulers and heirs from going unmarried
[*]Compatible with [b]any government type[/b] (monarchy, republic, tribe, steppe horde; theocracy support gated by church marriage laws)
[/list]

[h2]Compatibility[/h2]
Should be compatible with any mod. Adds a single new character interaction and a localization file with no base game files overridden.

Works alongside [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3606305941]Auto Noble Marriage[/url]. If that mod marries off your intended recipient before this interaction fires, the 25 ducats are automatically refunded.

[h2]Notes[/h2]
[list]
[*]Changes the checksum, so [b]no achievements[/b] can be earned with this mod active
[*]Save compatible, can be added to an existing save
[/list]

[h2]Open Source[/h2]
The source code is available on [url=https://github.com/JustinRudisal/marry-local-noble]GitHub[/url]. Pull requests and bug reports are welcome.
